## Section 4: Proposed autom8-asana-domain Skill

**Decision**: CREATE this skill

**Rationale**:
1. autom8_asana has significant SDK-specific knowledge Claude doesn't have:
   - SaveSession pattern (Unit of Work for Asana)
   - ActionOperation types (add_tag, move_to_section, add_comment, etc.)
   - Asana resource hierarchy (Workspace > Team > Project > Section > Task)
   - Batch API chunking semantics
   - Cache protocol extensibility
   - Async-first patterns with sync wrappers

2. The existing standards skill contains GENERIC patterns that are WRONG for this SDK

3. Precedent: charter-domain (1,097 lines), autom8-db-domain (400+ lines) both created value

### Proposed Structure

```
.claude/skills/autom8-asana-domain/
├── SKILL.md (80L)           # Entry point, activation triggers
├── context.md (120L)        # SDK overview (from PROJECT_CONTEXT.md, expanded)
├── glossary.md (100L)       # SaveSession, GID, ActionOperation, etc.
├── repository-map.md (80L)  # /batch, /cache, /clients, /models, /persistence, /protocols, /transport
├── code-patterns.md (100L)  # Async patterns, Pydantic v2, Protocol-based DI
├── asana-domain.md (100L)   # Resource taxonomy: Tasks, Projects, Sections, Custom Fields
└── tech-stack.md (80L)      # Python 3.10+, httpx, Pydantic v2, Polars, pytest-asyncio
```

**Total**: ~660 lines

### Skill SKILL.md Content

```yaml
---
name: autom8-asana-domain
description: "SDK-specific patterns for autom8_asana async Asana API client. Use when: working with SaveSession, batch operations, Asana resources, cache backends, async/sync patterns. Triggers: SaveSession, UoW, batch API, Asana task/project/section, GID, ActionOperation, cache protocol, async client."
---
```

### Activation Triggers

| Trigger | What Loads |
|---------|------------|
| "SaveSession", "unit of work", "batch save" | context.md, code-patterns.md |
| "Asana task", "Asana project", "custom field" | asana-domain.md, glossary.md |
| "where does this file go", "SDK structure" | repository-map.md |
| "cache", "Redis", "protocol" | tech-stack.md, code-patterns.md |
| "async", "sync wrapper" | code-patterns.md |

