## Appendix B: autom8-asana-domain Skill File Specifications

### SKILL.md (~80 lines)

```markdown
---
name: autom8-asana-domain
description: "SDK-specific patterns for autom8_asana async Asana API client. Use when: working with SaveSession, batch operations, Asana resources, cache backends, async/sync patterns. Triggers: SaveSession, UoW, batch API, Asana task/project/section, GID, ActionOperation, cache protocol, async client."
---

# autom8_asana SDK Domain

> Async-first Asana API client with Unit of Work pattern

## What This SDK Is

autom8_asana is a standalone Python SDK wrapper for the Asana API. It provides:
- **SaveSession**: Unit of Work pattern for batched operations
- **Resource Clients**: Type-safe access to Asana resources
- **Batch API**: Efficient bulk operations
- **Cache Protocol**: Pluggable caching backends

## Quick Reference

| I need to... | See |
|--------------|-----|
| Understand SDK structure | [repository-map.md](repository-map.md) |
| Work with SaveSession | [code-patterns.md](code-patterns.md) |
| Understand Asana resources | [asana-domain.md](asana-domain.md) |
| Check terminology | [glossary.md](glossary.md) |
| Check tech stack | [tech-stack.md](tech-stack.md) |

## Key Constraints

- **Python 3.10+** (not 3.12+)
- **Async-first** with sync wrappers for compatibility
- **No business logic** - pure API wrapper
- **Protocol-based DI** - consumers implement interfaces

## Progressive References

- [context.md](context.md) - Full SDK context and architecture
- [glossary.md](glossary.md) - SaveSession, GID, ActionOperation, etc.
- [repository-map.md](repository-map.md) - /batch, /cache, /clients, etc.
- [code-patterns.md](code-patterns.md) - Async patterns, Pydantic v2
- [asana-domain.md](asana-domain.md) - Tasks, Projects, Sections, Custom Fields
- [tech-stack.md](tech-stack.md) - httpx, Pydantic, Polars, pytest-asyncio
```

### repository-map.md (~80 lines)

```markdown
# autom8_asana Repository Map

> SDK directory structure

## Package Structure

```
/src/autom8_asana/
├── /batch              # Batch API client (bulk operations)
│   ├── client.py       # BatchClient for Asana batch endpoint
│   └── models.py       # BatchRequest, BatchResponse
│
├── /cache              # Cache layer
│   ├── backends/       # Redis, In-memory implementations
│   └── protocol.py     # CacheProtocol interface
│
├── /clients            # Resource-specific API clients
│   ├── base.py         # BaseClient with common methods
│   ├── tasks.py        # TasksClient
│   ├── projects.py     # ProjectsClient
│   └── ...             # Sections, Tags, Custom Fields, etc.
│
├── /dataframes         # Polars dataframe layer
│   └── ...             # DataFrame operations
│
├── /models             # Pydantic v2 models
│   ├── resources.py    # Task, Project, Section, etc.
│   ├── common.py       # NameGid, pagination types
│   └── ...
│
├── /observability      # Logging, metrics, tracing
│
├── /persistence        # SaveSession (Unit of Work)
│   ├── session.py      # SaveSession class
│   ├── tracker.py      # Change tracking
│   ├── models.py       # SaveOperation, SaveResult
│   ├── graph.py        # Dependency ordering (Kahn's algorithm)
│   ├── executor.py     # Batch execution
│   └── action_executor.py  # Action endpoint operations
│
├── /protocols          # Abstract interfaces
│   └── auth.py         # AuthProtocol for token providers
│
├── /transport          # HTTP layer
│   └── retry.py        # Retry with exponential backoff
│
├── __init__.py         # Public API exports
├── client.py           # AsanaClient (main entry point)
├── config.py           # Configuration
└── exceptions.py       # SDK exceptions
```

## Where to Put New Code

| I'm creating... | Put it in... |
|-----------------|--------------|
| New resource client | `/clients/{resource}.py` |
| Pydantic model | `/models/{resource}.py` |
| Cache backend | `/cache/backends/{backend}.py` |
| SaveSession enhancement | `/persistence/` |
| Transport modification | `/transport/` |

## Tests

```
/tests/
├── /unit/              # Pure logic tests
└── conftest.py         # Shared fixtures
```
```

